IN the INTEREST OF: I.W., Plaintiff, Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
C.W. (Father), Appellant. WD 81304 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: September 18, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied October 23, 2018 Mary S. Mann, for Respondent I.Q.W. Kathleen M. Hunter, for Respondent Juvenile Officer. Edward E. Moore, Kansas City, Co-counsel for Respondent Juvenile Officer. James R. Craft, for Appellant. Before Division Two: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, Lisa White Hardwick, Judge and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Father appeals the trial court's judgment terminating his parental rights to his minor child, I.W. Finding no error, we affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
